A message to creators and entrepreneurs…

One of my latest dancing videos has gone viral. It’s inches away from hitting over 400,000 views.

BUT that video would not have gone viral if I did not post it! And posting as a creator or beginning entrepreneur can be the hardest thing to do!

Feeling hopeless, depressed and stuck is what inspired @theloveniablog 🤎 My mindset was disallowing me to post, therefore I know others were going through it too. I want to support this community, encourage and inspire you all to POST YOUR WORK. 

Sometimes, it’s easier said than done. That’s why I’d like to be in your corner as a support system🤞🏾

If you haven’t found the means to share your work, it’s okay. You will find it. For now, give yourself the time and healing you need to set your mind free. And keep God in the midst of it!!!!!

The battle is in the MIND. But I want you to know you are not fighting alone.

Journal 49 | Talking Vs. Praying

[Date and Time N/A]

I look at moments in this past month and year that were authentic. Moments where I was excited, or grateful. But just good, honest moments. I’m glad I have footage for it too. This is not like normal journals, but it sat well with me. 

My fast ended last week, and the most valuable thing I can reflect on are my conversations with God. From talking to Him, He makes me value mundane moments. 
I value the good people in my life. I value growth. I value adaptation. And I value this relationship I’ve built with myself. I’ve come a long way. But the devotion is real🤎 cheers to lovin yoselffff!

This year has been life changing and eye-opening. I put myself out there and got so much back—including you all💖 Anything is possible! Cheers to 2024 and the best yet🥂

"How are you able to just post yourself dancing? I'm so scared to do that."

It's the most asked question I've gotten within these last few months. It's kind of weird because I admire the question, but I don't know how to answer it...yet? lol

I could tell you "just record yourself dancing!" or "have confidence in yourself" or whatever else shallow response, but it's deeper than just having a piece of content to post. I think it's that I've found my happy. And finding that is work that we all have to do. Once you find yours, the game changes. 

I guess tonight is not about how music makes me feel, but rather how I make myself feel. Can you tell how I make myself feel? Can you tell the relationship I have with myself? Listening to music doesn't make me happy. Dancing doesn't make me happy. Sharing media online doesn't make me happy. I'm happy... so I dance, listen to music and share media with the world. 

It's a real world out here-offline, behind the cameras, behind closed doors. Not to be morbid, but just keeping it real...suicide rates are high. This world is becoming unlivable for some, that they rather be dead than to live another day. So in real life, I want to make sure I'm smiling and living and being. That what I share on here are glimpses of that, not a facade. 

Tonight, if I could offer any advice: success is not pleasing anyone on social media with the dopest content and creating the best illusion. 

Success is when you find yourself and learn how to make you happy. It's becoming the person that makes you smile, makes you feel alive, makes you feel seen, heard, valued. There's power in becoming the person you thought someone else needed to be for you. Please don't let that go over your head🙏🏾 

I found my power and I got every reason to dance about it! If you read this whole message, thank you. Feel free to share your takeaway. Y'all know I love talking in the comments❤️

Sending love to everybody. Take it easy!!!!❤️✨
